	Going
	Concern





	 


	 




	At present, we have no
	enough cash to pay for our selling, general and administrative expenses. As
	such, in order to continue developing our operations as planned, we may be
	reliant on obtaining additional funding by private placement of our equity
	securities and/or obtaining the loan by mortgage our land. But, there can be no
	assurance we will be funded as such. Thus, there can be no assurance we will
	successfully continue our operation and/or complete our plan of operations


	. 


	Based on these assumptions, our auditor has
	expressed doubt about our ability to continue as a going concern.




	 


	 





